#: ../../P/phase.rst:5
msgid "phase"
msgstr "phase"

#: ../../P/phase.rst:7
msgid ""
"n\\. The offset of one's waking-sleeping schedule with respect to the "
"standard 24-hour cycle; a useful concept among people who often work at "
"night and/or according to no fixed schedule. It is not uncommon to change "
"one's phase by as much as 6 hours per day on a regular basis. \"What's your "
"phase?\" \"I've been getting in about 8PM lately, but I'm going to "
":ref:`wrap-around` to the day schedule by Friday.\" A person who is roughly "
"12 hours out of phase is sometimes said to be in night mode. (The term day "
"mode is also (but less frequently) used, meaning you're working 9 to 5 (or, "
"more likely, 10 to 6).) The act of altering one's cycle is called changing "
"phase; phase shifting has also been recently reported from Caltech."
msgstr ""
"名詞 "
"標準的な24時間周期に対する、自分の起きている・寝ているスケジュールのずれ。夜に、または決まったスケジュールなしに働くことが多い人々の間で有用な概念。日常的に位相を1日あたり6時間も変えることは珍しくない。「君の位相は?」「最近は夜8時くらいに来てるけど、金曜までには昼間のスケジュールに\\"
" :ref:`wrap-around`\\ するつもりだ」位相がおよそ12時間ずれている人は、night modeにあると言われることがある。(day "
"modeという用語も(より頻度は低いが)使われ、9時から5時(あるいはもっとありそうなのは10時から6時)まで働いていることを意味する。)自分の周期を変える行為はchanging"
" phaseと呼ばれる。phase shiftingも最近Caltechから報告されている。"

#: ../../P/phase.rst:16
msgid ""
"change phase the hard way: To stay awake for a very long time in order to "
"get into a different phase."
msgstr "change phase the hard way:別の位相に入るために、非常に長い時間起き続けること。"

#: ../../P/phase.rst:18
msgid ""
"change phase the easy way: To stay asleep, etc. However, some claim that "
"either staying awake longer or sleeping longer is easy, and that it is "
"*shortening* your day or night that is really hard (see :ref:`wrap-"
"around`\\). The ‘jet lag’ that afflicts travelers who cross many time-zone "
"boundaries may be attributed to two distinct causes: the strain of travel "
"per se, and the strain of changing phase. Hackers who suddenly find that "
"they must change phase drastically in a short period of time, particularly "
"the hard way, experience something very like jet lag without traveling."
msgstr ""
"change phase the easy way:眠り続けることなど。しかし、起き続けるか眠り続けるかのどちらかは簡単で、本当に難しいのは1日や1晩を"
" *短くする* ことだと主張する人もいる(\\ :ref:`wrap-around`\\ "
"を参照)。多くの時間帯の境界を越える旅行者を苦しめる‘時差ぼけ’は、二つの別個の原因に帰せられるかもしれない。旅行そのものの負担と、位相を変えることの負担である。突然、短期間で位相を大幅に、特にhard"
" wayで変えなければならなくなったハッカーは、旅行せずとも時差ぼけによく似た何かを経験する。"
